- content_for(:title, "Demo")

%p
  This page contains a demo of some of the web libraries and technologies I'm
  currently familiar with.

%p
  (Okay, honestly this is really basically just a way to satisfy all the
  assignment requirements. I couln't find a natural way to integrate stuff like
  jQuery, LetteringJS, or HTML5 audio into a website about my professional
  portfolio. Especially given that the site is already using Polymer under the
  hood.)

%section
  %h2 Form

  Here's an example of a form!

  %form{method: "post"}
    .form-item
      %paper-input{label:"Your Name"}

    .form-item
      %label
        T-Shirt size
        %br
        %paper-radio-group{:selected => "small"}
          %paper-radio-button{:label => "Small", :name => "small"}
          %br
          %paper-radio-button{:label => "Medium", :name => "medium"}
          %br
          %paper-radio-button{:label => "Large", :name => "large"}

    .form-item
      %label
        T-Shirt quantity
        %br
        %paper-slider{min: 0, max: 10, step: 1, pin: true, snaps: true}

    .form-item
      %label
        Delivery date
        %br
        %input{type: "date", name: "delivery"}
      %br
      (No Polymer element for this yet, sadly.)

    .form-item
      %label
        T-shirt color
        %br
        %input{type: "color", name: "color"}

    .form-item
      %input{type: "submit"}

